<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="343" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="343">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="343">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Iridaceae" genus="Merodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Merodon pulveris" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulveris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">Merodon pulveris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a medium sized species (11-12 mm). It can be separated from 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="M." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="M. calcaratus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calcaratus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">M. calcaratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its longer antenna (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Antenna. A, B, J Merodon natans C, D, K M. pulveris E, F, I M. makrisi Vujic, Radenkovic &amp; Tot sp. nov. G, H M. calcaratus; A, C, E, G male B, D, F, H-K female; A-H lateral view I-K dorsal view; A Greece (Olimp) B Greece (Achaia) C, D Turkey E, F, I Cyprus G, H Spain J Greece (Alexandroupoli) K Turkey. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e65861.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/576175" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">2C, D</figureCitation>
), broader metafemur in both sexes (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Metaleg without tarsomeres, lateral view. A, B Merodon natans C, D M. pulveris E, F M. makrisi Vujic, Radenkovic &amp; Tot sp. nov. G, H M. calcaratus; A, C, E, G male B, D, F, H female; A Italy (Sicily) B Croatia C, D Turkey E, F Cyprus G Algeria H Tunis. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e65861.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/576177" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">4C, D</figureCitation>
) and the large, rounded posterior surstyle lobe (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Epandrium, lateral view. A, B Merodon natans C M. pulveris D M. makrisi Vujic, Radenkovic &amp; Tot sp. nov. Abbreviation: v - triangular prominence on ventral margin of posterior surstyle lobe; A Greece (Achaia) B Montenegro C Greece (Rhodes) D Cyprus. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e65861.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/576183" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">10C</figureCitation>
) of the male genitalia (in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="M." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="M. calcaratus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calcaratus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">M. calcaratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
narrow, fingerlike; Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Merodon calcaratus epandrium, lateral view. A Morocco B, D Algeria C Tunis E left surstyle of specimen from Kenya F Kenya G Spain. Arrow marks invagination on ventral margin of surstyle. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e65861.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/576178" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">5A-G</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Iridaceae" genus="Merodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Merodon pulveris" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulveris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">Merodon pulveris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="M." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="M. natans" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="natans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">M. natans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="M." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="M. makrisi" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="makrisi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">M. makrisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., but differs by the following characters of the male genitalia: ventral margin of posterior surstyle lobe with distinct triangular prominence (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Epandrium, lateral view. A, B Merodon natans C M. pulveris D M. makrisi Vujic, Radenkovic &amp; Tot sp. nov. Abbreviation: v - triangular prominence on ventral margin of posterior surstyle lobe; A Greece (Achaia) B Montenegro C Greece (Rhodes) D Cyprus. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e65861.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/576183" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">10C</figureCitation>
:v), in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="M." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="M. natans" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="natans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">M. natans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without visible triangular prominence from lateral view (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Epandrium, lateral view. A, B Merodon natans C M. pulveris D M. makrisi Vujic, Radenkovic &amp; Tot sp. nov. Abbreviation: v - triangular prominence on ventral margin of posterior surstyle lobe; A Greece (Achaia) B Montenegro C Greece (Rhodes) D Cyprus. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e65861.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/576183" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">10A, B</figureCitation>
), it can be present in some specimens, but it is small and visible only from ventral view (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Epandrium, lateral view. A, B Merodon natans C M. pulveris D M. makrisi Vujic, Radenkovic &amp; Tot sp. nov. Abbreviation: v - triangular prominence on ventral margin of posterior surstyle lobe; A Greece (Achaia) B Montenegro C Greece (Rhodes) D Cyprus. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e65861.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/576183" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">10A, B</figureCitation>
); posterior surstyle lobe broader and shorter (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Epandrium, lateral view. A, B Merodon natans C M. pulveris D M. makrisi Vujic, Radenkovic &amp; Tot sp. nov. Abbreviation: v - triangular prominence on ventral margin of posterior surstyle lobe; A Greece (Achaia) B Montenegro C Greece (Rhodes) D Cyprus. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e65861.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/576183" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">10C</figureCitation>
), narrower and more elongated in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="M." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="M. makrisi" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="makrisi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">M. makrisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Merodon makrisi Vujic, Radenkovic &amp; Tot sp. nov. male genitalia, Cyprus. A epandrium B left surstyle C, E hypandrium D aedeagus and associated structures; A, C, D lateral view B, E ventral view. Abbreviations: a - anterior surstyle lobe, aa - aedeagal apodeme, ae - aedeagus, c - cercus, ea - ejaculatory apodeme, la - lateral sclerite of aedeagus, n - notch on theca to which is attached the aedeagal apodeme, p - posterior surstyle lobe, v - triangular prominence on ventral margin of posterior surstyle lobe. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e65861.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/576181" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">8A</figureCitation>
:p, B:p, 10D). Fossette position medially between the base of the arista and apex of basoflagellomere distinguishes females of this species from 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="M." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="M. makrisi" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="makrisi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">M. makrisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov (in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="M." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="M. makrisi" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="makrisi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">M. makrisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov position of fossette is near base of arista (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Antenna. A, B, J Merodon natans C, D, K M. pulveris E, F, I M. makrisi Vujic, Radenkovic &amp; Tot sp. nov. G, H M. calcaratus; A, C, E, G male B, D, F, H-K female; A-H lateral view I-K dorsal view; A Greece (Olimp) B Greece (Achaia) C, D Turkey E, F, I Cyprus G, H Spain J Greece (Alexandroupoli) K Turkey. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e65861.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/576175" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">2I</figureCitation>
:f)). From 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="M." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="M. natans" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="natans">
