<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="343" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="343">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="343">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Iridaceae" genus="Merodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Merodon pulveris" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulveris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">Merodon pulveris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
inhabits the Anatolian Peninsula, the eastern Mediterranean islands (Lesvos, Samos, Rhodes) and Cyprus, but is absent from southern and western Europe as opposed to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="M." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="M. natans" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="natans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">M. natans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Distribution map of the species of Merodon natans group." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e65861.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/576179" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="343" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="343">Biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="343">
Preferred environments (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Merodon pulveris. A male on Drimia aphylla, in Cyprus, photo: C. Makris, 6 Oct. 2016 B female in Cyprus, photo: C. Makris, 20 Oct. 2013 C typical habitat in Agiassos (Lesvos, Greece) where M. pulveris can be collected, photo: D. Vujanovic." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e65861.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/576185" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">12C</figureCitation>
) are open areas in Eastern European maquis on limestone near coniferous forests with large populations of its host plant 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Hyacinthaceae" genus="Prospero" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Prospero autumnale" order="Agavales" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="autumnale">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">Prospero autumnale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2735.1.5" author="Radenkovic, S" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" pagination="35 - 56" refId="B47" refString="Radenkovic, S, Vujic, A, Stahls, G, Perez-Banon, C, Rojo, S, Petanidou, T, Simic, S, 2011. Three new cryptic species of the genus Merodon Meigen (Diptera: Syrphidae) from the island of Lesvos (Greece). Zootaxa 2735: 35 - 56, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2735.1.5" title="Three new cryptic species of the genus Merodon Meigen (Diptera: Syrphidae) from the island of Lesvos (Greece)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2735.1.5" volume="2735" year="2011">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Radenković">Radenkovic</normalizedToken>
et al. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
). Flowers visited include: 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Foeniculum" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Foeniculum" order="Apiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">Foeniculum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Hyacinthaceae" genus="Prospero" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Prospero autumnale" order="Agavales" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="autumnale">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">Prospero autumnale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.20363/BZB-2019.68.1.125" author="van Steenis, J" journalOrPublisher="Bonn zoological Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" pagination="125 - 146" refId="B84" refString="van Steenis, J, van Zuijen, MP, van Steenis, W, Makris, C, van Eck, A, Mengual, X, 2019. Hoverflies (Diptera: Syrphidae) of Cyprus: results from a collecting trip in October 2017. Bonn zoological Bulletin 68 (1): 125 - 146, DOI: https://doi.org/10.20363/BZB-2019.68.1.125" title="Hoverflies (Diptera: Syrphidae) of Cyprus: results from a collecting trip in October 2017." url="https://doi.org/10.20363/BZB-2019.68.1.125" volume="68" year="2019">van Steenis et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Drimia" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Drimia aphylla" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aphylla">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">Drimia aphylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Merodon pulveris. A male on Drimia aphylla, in Cyprus, photo: C. Makris, 6 Oct. 2016 B female in Cyprus, photo: C. Makris, 20 Oct. 2013 C typical habitat in Agiassos (Lesvos, Greece) where M. pulveris can be collected, photo: D. Vujanovic." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e65861.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/576185" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">12A</figureCitation>
). Flight period is in spring (April-May) and autumn (late September/mid October). The larva described here was found in 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Hyacinthaceae" genus="Prospero" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Prospero autumnale" order="Agavales" pageId="0" pageNumber="343" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="autumnale">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="343">Prospero autumnale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on Lesvos island in Greece.
</paragraph>
